From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dominik Grzegorzek <dominik.grzegorzek@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 22 Feb 2024 15:12:37 +0100
Subject: drm/xe/eudebug/xe3p: Per context debugging support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

xe3p is the first platform introducing the per-context debugging
feature. Control over the EU workload has transitioned from KMD to GuC,
transforming eu_control into an interface for GuC. As a result,
attention becomes invisible for XE, and the EU attention event will
no longer be sent. Instead, the drm_xe_eudebug_event_sync_host has
been added, triggered every time GuC sends a notification about
a stopped context.

The EXEC_QUEUE_EUDEBUG_FLAG_ENABLE flag no longer sets runalone
from xe3p onwards, as it is no longer necessary. Instead,
it marks the exec_queue as debuggable in GuC before execution.

Furthermore, from xe3p onwards, after interrupting threads,
the user needs to resume the interrupt prior to clearing attentions
to prevent further exceptions. To facilitate this, the new
DRM_XE_EUDEBUG_EU_CONTROL_CMD_UNLOCK has been added.
Note that DRM_XE_EUDEBUG_EU_CONTROL_CMD_RESUME retains its original
meaning, so it clears attentions for given lrc.

v2: checkpatch (Maciej)

v3: adapted to eudebug v3 (Maciej)

v4: rework after review (Maciej)

v5: fix oops

v6: added kunit test

v7: fixed oops from accessing closed file data (Andrzej)
